    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Workflow B2 — Shorts Poster\n\n**Schedule:** cron fires 3x/day at 09:00, 13:00, 19:00 (`0 9,13,19 * * *`). Each fire posts exactly ONE video. The Manual Trigger is there for testing.\n\n**Run order:** A (Indexer) → A2 (Planner) → B1 (Generator) → **B2 (Poster)**\n\n### What each run does\n1. Reads `video_queue`, picks ONE random row with `status = approved`.\n2. If none → Telegram warning, exit.\n3. Downloads that MP4 from the `finished_videos` Drive folder.\n4. Uploads it to YouTube as a public Short.\n5. Sets the queue row `status = posted`, fills `posted_at` + `youtube_url`.\n6. Sets the matching `content_plan` row `status = posted`.\n7. Telegram confirmation, including how many approved videos remain (warns if below `QUEUE_LOW_THRESHOLD`).\n\n### Your approval step (between B1 and B2)\nOpen `video_queue`, watch each `pending_review` video via its Drive link, and set `status` to `approved` or `rejected` by hand. Only `approved` rows get posted.\n\n### Setup\n- Fill `QUEUE_SHEET_ID`, `CONTENT_PLAN_SHEET_ID`, `TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID` in Globals.\n- Set credentials on the YouTube, Telegram, Drive, and Sheets nodes (replace the REPLACE_WITH_* placeholders by re-selecting the credential).\n- YouTube OAuth2 needs the YouTube Data API v3 enabled in Google Cloud Console.\n\n### Note on row matching\nThe queue write-back matches on `video_drive_id` (unique per row). The content_plan write-back matches on `chapter_number` + `concept_index`. If you run multiple books whose chapter numbers collide, add `drive_file_id` to the queue row in B1 and include it here as a third matching column for safety.\n\n### YouTube API quota\nEach upload costs ~1600 units of the 10,000/day default quota. 3 posts/day = ~4800 units. Fine. Don't batch-post more than ~6/day without a quota increase.",
